In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 11, 2014, as Veterans Day. He pays tribute to the men and women who have served in the American military and highlights their sacrifices in defending the nation's freedom. The President emphasizes the importance of supporting veterans as they transition back to civilian life, including providing resources and benefits such as healthcare and education. He also calls on Americans to honor and appreciate veterans through public ceremonies, private prayers, and patriotic activities. The article concludes with the official proclamation of Veterans Day as a legal public holiday.